	Your sword is glowing very brightly.
message.des.411
	Your sword is brilliantly lit.
message.des.412
	A secret tunnel descends into darkness.
message.des.413
	A rope hangs from the window.
message.des.414
	The werewolf snarls as he wards off your attack.
message.des.415
	The butler has a black belt and repels your attack.
message.des.416
	Attack the bat??  That's gross.  I won't do it.
message.des.417
	The shutters are closed.
message.des.418
	Kill what, fool?
message.des.419
	The blade does not penetrate the bat's thick hide.
message.des.420
	Werewolves can only be killed with silver.
message.des.421
	A smiling hunchback is following you.
message.des.422
	You attack the hunchback and break his neck.
message.des.423
	The coffin is closed.
message.des.424
	The Count is asleep in the coffin.
message.des.425
	The Count is frightened by the cross and cowers in the coffin.
message.des.426
	The Count sits up and prepares for breakfast-namely you!
message.des.427
	The vampire is gone for good (Ding Dong, the Count is dead).
message.des.428
	Something on the ground outside is glistening brightly.
message.des.429
	The hunchback drives away the werewolf and dies in the struggle.
message.died.7001
	You leap through the open window and are\ndashed into pieces on the rocks below.
message.died.7004
	A thick black smoke fills the room, engulfing you in\nlethal choking fumes (smoking is bad for your health).
message.died.7007
	You leap into the pit and fall for hours.  You land\non some moist "undead" bodies and are eaten alive.
message.died.7010
	My, My.  You seem to have bitten the dust.\nI can attempt to reincarnate you, but I'm\nnot very good at it.  Should I try?
message.died.7013
	You fall weightlessly through a thick mist.\nYour head is spinning as you emerge and find...
message.died.7015
	You seem to have died again.  I can try and\nreincarnate you, but you're taxing my patience.\nWould you like me to try??
message.died.7018
	You float aimlessly through a green mist which\ntranscends time and space.  You regain your\nsenses and realize that ...
message.died.7021
	You did it again, didn't you? I'm afraid that\nall the mist has evaporated.  I'm so sorry,\nbut this means you are dead for good.
message.died.7024
	You have fallen in the dark and broken your neck.
message.gnome.1001
	There is an ugly little gnome in the room with you!
message.gnome.1002
	IT GETS YOU!!
message.gnome.1003
	It misses by an elf-hair!
message.gnome.1004
	He shoots a poisoned dart at you!
message.hint.1
	A werewolf can be killed with a silver bullet.
message.hint.2
	A vampire can be killed with a wooden stake.
message.hint.3
	A well fed hunchback is an asset in the castle.
message.hint.4
	The rope can be used to climb out the bedroom window.
message.hint.5
	The butler can write notes, if given the tools.
message.hint.6
	The bottle can hold liquids, such as blood or water.
message.hint.7
	The cross will immobilize the vampire.
message.hint.8
	The acid will dissolve the bars over the window.
message.hint.9
	Water will extinguish a troublesome fire.
message.hint.10
	The surgeon general has warned you about smoking.
message.hint.11
	The werewolf can be killed with a silver bullet.
message.hint.12
	You can get out the window by dissolving the bars.
message.hint.13
	The count can only be killed with a stake through the heart.
message.hint.14
	Try opening the book by shakespeare.
message.hint.15
	There's a surprise in the drawer.
message.hint.16
	The butler can write notes if he has the proper tools.
message.hint.17
	Try breaking the mirror in the single mirror chamber.
message.hint.18
	Acid will dissolve the bars and clear the window.
message.hint.19
	The bat will leave after it has been fed.
message.hint.20
	You need an axe or something to break the boards.
message.hint.21
	You'll have to get out of the maze on your own.
message.hint.22
	I think there is something behind the ice.
message.hint.23
	Try "smoking" him out.
message.hint.24
	Gnomes are a problem, but you can "give" them the axe.
message.hint.25
	The torch can generate a lot of heat (but not light).
message.hint.26
	The hook is useful for scaling steep walls.
message.hint.27
	Try thinking of some way to get through the ice.
message.hint.28
	The wizard can be overcome by magic, not by force.
message.hint.29
	Your lamp can operate on fossil fuels.
message.hint.30
	You are in a remote castle somewhere in Eastern Europe.\nI will be your eyes and hands.  Direct me with words such\nas "LOOK", "TAKE", or "DROP".  To move, enter compass points\n(N,NE,E,SE,S,SW,W,NW), UP, or DOWN.  To get a list of what\nyou are carrying, say "INVENTORY".  To save the current game\nso it can be finished later say "SAVE".  Say "RESTORE" as\nyour first command to finish a game that had been saved.
message.hint.31
	The object of the game is to find the master of the castle\nand kill him, while accumulating as many treasures as possible.\nYou get maximum points for depositing the treasures in the\nvault.  Notice that the descriptions of treasures have an\nexclamation point.  Be wary, as many dangers await you in\nin the castle.
message.hint.32
	To supress the long room descriptions, type "BRIEF".  To\nreturn to the long room descriptions, use the command "LONG".\n"SCORE" will give you your present score in the game.  "HELP"\nwill give you a hint about an object in the room, but it will\ncost you some points.  To end your explorations, say "QUIT".\nGood luck. (you'll need it).
message.hint.33
	To aid you in your travels, you may ask for a hint by\nsaying "HINT object", where "object" is the item that you\nneed help with (e.g. "HELP CROSS").  Saying "HELP ROOM"\nwill give you some help concerning the room you're in.
message.hint.1001
	Would you like more detailed instructions?
message.hint.1002
	Sorry, not available.
message.hint.1003
	It will cost you five points.\nDo you still want the hint?.
message.hours.1002
	I'M SORRY, BUT THE CASTLE IS CLOSED RIGHT NOW.\nCASTLE HOURS ARE :\nMONDAY THRU FRIDAY-----21:00 TO 09:00\nSAT. AND SUN.-----ALL DAY\n\nONLY BARONS MAY PLAY AT THIS TIME.\nARE YOU A BARON???
message.hours.1003
	PROVE IT BY ENTERING THE SECRET WORD.
message.hours.1005
	THAT IS NOT THE SECRET WORD.  BYE BYE.
message.restore.3005
	I can't do that at this point in time.
message.wolf.1001
	There is a fearsome werewolf in the room with you!
message.wolf.1002
	The werewolf attacks you with its sharp claw!
message.wolf.1003
	It severs your jugular vein and mortally wounds you!
message.wolf.1004
	It just misses your neck!
message.wolf.1005
	A nasty werewolf lunges at you, takes a swipe at\nyour neck, misses and runs away.
message.yorn.2001
	Please answer YES or NO !
