room.80.longdesc
	You are in the remains of an old wine cellar, apparantly the\nvictim of a cave in.  Casks of once fine wine lie crushed in\nthe rubble.  A battered keg of GENESEE sits off in the corner.\nThe room smells like a Rathskellar band party.  A muddy path\ngoes east, and steps lead up to a door in the ceiling.
room.80.shortdesc
	You are in the wine cellar.
room.81.door
	-1
room.81.longdesc
	You are on a small island near a large waterfall.  The sound of\ncrashing surf can be clearly heard, although you cannot quite\nmake out the form of the waterfall through the thick mist.  A\nmessage traced out in the sand reads "GILLIGAN WAS HERE".  There\nare pieces of a wreck (the S.S. MINNOW?) scattered about.
room.81.shortdesc
	You are on the island near the falls.
